x rope structures prior to both flares which are\nsubsequently supported by the observations of the eruption of hot EUV channels.\nThe second X-class flare diverged from the standard flare scenario in the\nevolution of two sets of flare ribbons, that are spatially well separated,\nproviding firm evidence of magnetic reconnections at two coronal heights.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 31 Oct 2018 08:07:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-12-26"}
