pectra simultaneously. We determine\nTeff , log g and [M/H] for 292 M dwarfs of spectral type M0 to M9, where the\nformation of dust and clouds are important. The derived Teff for the sample\nranges from 2300 to 4000 K, values of log g ranges from 4.5 geq log g leq 5.5\nand the resulting metallicity ranges from -0.5 geq [M/H] leq +0.5. We have also\nexplored the possible differences in Teff , log g and [M/H] by comparing them\nwith other studies of the same sample of M dwarfs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 31 Oct 2018 12:41:26 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 2 Nov 2018 11:16:33 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 28 Dec 2018 08:14:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-02-20"}
